{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e36f7c7c-a142-445c-9c37-0c0b4d84ceb4","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8\">\n\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net9.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n</Project>\n```\n\n`MSTest.Sdk` replaces the standard `Microsoft.NET.Sdk` — it automatically pulls in MSTest runner, framework, and analyzers. No extra `<PackageReference>` items needed.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings`)\n\nCreate a `my.runsettings` file (or add to an existing one):\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>          <!-- 0 = one worker per core -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>    <!-- or ClassLevel -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nOr skip the file and use the assembly-level attribute approach — add this anywhere (e.g., a `Usings.cs`):\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.MethodLevel)]\n```\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your integration test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public async Task CanInsertAndQuery()\n    {\n        // This will NOT run in parallel with other tests\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` works at the **class** or **method** level.\n- Those tests run **after** all parallelizable tests complete, on a single thread.\n- Everything else still runs in parallel across all available cores.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fc8174dd-9221-4799-a58c-2c9b0361c817","outputTokens":473,"requestId":"5812:38FB84:5A09EFD:6200DF7:6A033948"},"id":"eefb9911-077c-48f2-821f-d0af87f17ec2","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:29:39.331Z","parentId":"a8394b86-1104-40ff-a1e7-d05b530866d4"}
